# Git Branch Workflow

Before making any code edits, check the current git branch:

1. Run `git branch --show-current`
2. If branch is `main` or `master`: **do not edit**. Tell the user to create a feature branch first 
   (e.g. `git checkout -b feature/description` or `git worktree add ../new-feature -b feature/description`).
3. If on a feature branch: proceed with edits

Skip this check only if the workspace is not a git repo (`git rev-parse --is-inside-work-tree` ≠ true).
